  "texts": [
    "Efforts have also been made to augment the efficiency of these models, particularly in reducing the latency in response generation, which is crucial for real-time applications [20], [21], [22].",
    "Research has also explored the application of deep learning in domain-specific LLMs, tailoring models to specific fields such as legal or medical language processing, thereby enhancing their precision and utility in specialized areas [23], [24], [25], [26].",
    "The adaptation of deep learning models for multilingual processing has been another area of focus, aiming to create LLMs that can understand and generate text in multiple languages with high accuracy [27], [28].",
    "Studies have also looked into the ethical implications of LLMs, particularly in terms of bias and fairness, leading to the development of methods to mitigate bias in language models [29], [30].",
    "Symbolic Reasoning in AISymbolic reasoning in AI has been explored as a means to incorporate logic and rule-based decision-making into intelligent systems."
